Class FunctorError

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Error
        • io.github.prolobjectlink.prolog.PrologError
          • io.github.prolobjectlink.prolog.FunctorError
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable

    public final class FunctorError
extends PrologError
    Runtime error raised when occurs one call to get functor method over a term that no have functor property. The functor is a compound term and atom property only. This runtime error is raised when we invoke PrologTerm.getFunctor() over terms like Numbers and Variables
    Since:
    1.0
    Author:
    Jose Zalacain
